<refsect1>
<title>Description</title>

<para>These functions are used for selecting or getting the current
buffers, when using the <link linkend="frames">multiple buffering</link>
function of LibGGI.
</para>

<para><function/ggiSetDisplayFrame/ sets the frame that gets displayed.  </para>
<para>
<function/ggiSetWriteFrame/ sets the frame for write operations such as
<function/ggiPuts/ and <function/ggiHLine/.
</para>
<para>
<function/ggiSetReadFrame/ sets the frame for read operations, like
<function/ggiGetPixel/ and the <function/ggiCrossBlit/ source.
</para>
<para><function/ggiGetDisplayFrame/ reports the frame currently displayed.  </para>
<para><function/ggiGetWriteFrame/ reports the frame currently written to.  </para>
<para><function/ggiSetReadFrame/ reports the frame currently read from.</para>

<para>
Frames are numbered from 0 to the number of frames requested - 1.
</para>

</refsect1>

<refsect1>
<title>Return value</title>

<para>The <function/ggiSet*Frame/ functions return <ReturnValue/0/ if they
succeed, and <ReturnValue><0</ReturnValue> if they fail.
</para>
<para>The <function/ggiGet*Frame/ functions never fail.
</para>

</refsect1>
